data.title: Racey Helps
data.meta_description: Felix Feldmaus als Retter by Racey Helps and a great selection of related books, art and collectibles available now at AbeBooks.co.uk.
data.text:
Condition: acceptable. Ausreichend/Acceptable: Exemplar mit vollständigem Text und sämtlichen Abbildungen oder Karten. Schmutztitel oder Vorsatz können fehlen. Einband bzw. Schutzumschlag weisen unter Umständen starke Gebrauchsspuren auf. / Describes a book or dust jacket that has the complete text pages (including those with maps or plates) but may lack endpapers, half-title, etc. (which must be noted). Binding, dust jacket (if any), etc may also be worn.

Condition: Good. 1970. No edition remarks. 24 pages. Paperback book with pictorial cover. Contains colour illustrations throughout. Pages remain bright and clear. Pages have mild foxing throughout. Previous owner's inscription to first page. Paper cover has mild edge wear with mild corner curling. Notable creasing to covers and spine. Mild tanning to spine and cover edges.

Condition: Fair. 1953. No Edition Remarks. 46 pages. No dust jacket. Green cloth. Colour illustrations throughout. Binding remains firm. Pages and illustrations have light tanning and foxing throughout. Previous owner's inscription to front free endpaper. Boards have light shelf-wear with corner bumping. Very slight crushing to spine ends. Creasing to front board. Light wear marks overall. Book has slight forward lean.

Paperback. Condition: Used; Very Good. ***Simply Brit*** Welcome to our online used book store, where affordability meets great quality. Dive into a world of captivating reads without breaking the bank. We take pride in offering a wide selection of used books, from classics to hidden gems, ensuring there is something for every literary palate. All orders are shipped within 24 hours and our lightning fast-delivery within 48 hours coupled with our prompt customer service ensures a smooth journey from ordering to delivery. Discover the joy of reading with us, your trusted source for affordable books that do not compromise on quality.

Condition: Fair. 1967. 48 pages. No dust jacket. Blue pictorial cloth. Pages are lightly tanned and thumbed at the edges, with light foxing. Binding has remained firm. Pen marks to a few pages. Boards are a little rub worn with slight shelf wear to corners, spine and edges. Corners are a little bumped. Spine ends are a mildly crushed, with small splits and chips. Pen scribbles to boards. Tanning to spine and edges. Boards are bowed. Book has a forward lean. Water marks to boards and spine.

No Binding. Condition: Very Good. The Three Stooges were busy, so she called on the next cheapest contractors she found online. Unmailed, very nice condition.

Hardcover. Condition: Good. No Jacket. Helps, Racey (illustrator). Not dated, approx 1950s. 78pp. Good/None. hard pictorial boards illustrated by Racey Helps, minor rubbing/chipping to edges, minor soiling/scuffing. Contents generally clean and tight but for minor soiling/spotting, minor browning. Owners name to title page. Decorative endpapers. Charming B&W illustrations throughout. Retellings of 10 of Grimm's perennially popular fairy tales.
